claim: Vaccination with a higher-dose recombinant flu vaccine may induce a more robust antibody response than egg-based standard-dose vaccines.
explanation: CONSORT flow diagram showing Year 1 (2018–2019) and Year 2 (2019–2020) participants re‐enrolled and randomized into three vaccine groups: IIV4 (egg‐based standard‐dose inactivated influenza), ccIIV4 (cell‐culture based inactivated influenza), and RIV4 (recombinant hemagglutinin influenza vaccine). It shows numbers randomized, re‐randomized, and excluded per protocol criteria. The figure is a participant flow diagram and does not present any antibody titer or immunogenicity data comparing RIV4 to egg‐based IIV4, so it does not support the claim. Note: No immunogenicity results are shown; only enrollment and randomization numbers are presented.
